14:38.711 --> 14:41.043
I'm thinking about
giving the baby up for adoption.

14:42.840 --> 14:44.501
Why? Why--?

14:45.551 --> 14:48.384
-Why would you do that?
-Take another look at the list.

14:48.554 --> 14:51.466
I mean, there are only three pros
and maybe--

14:51.641 --> 14:54.098
I can probably think of 100 cons.

14:54.310 --> 14:56.016
I'm a felon.

14:56.562 --> 14:59.349
-People hate me. I'm a pariah.
-Here, in DC

14:59.565 --> 15:03.524
That is why we have to move.
And the rest? Dangerous job, fixable.

15:03.694 --> 15:08.529
-Unmarried, totally fixable.
-Unmarried was never a part of my list.

15:08.699 --> 15:11.281
Well, a guy can dream, can't he?

15:11.494 --> 15:16.079
Yeah. Yeah, they're all fixable, Tom,
except for one:

15:17.333 --> 15:18.948
Reddington.

15:19.127 --> 15:20.333
We can get away from him.

15:20.503 --> 15:24.212
His life, my life,
is so filled with violence...

15:24.382 --> 15:31.003
...and anger and hatred and death.
How can I bring a child into that world?

15:32.306 --> 15:35.298
-My world.
-Our world, Liz...

15:35.518 --> 15:36.553
...not his. Ours.

15:36.727 --> 15:39.890
This is why I didn't tell you.
I knew you'd be annoyingly positive.

15:40.106 --> 15:43.189
-What, you don't want to be positive?
-I don't want to be naive.

15:43.734 --> 15:45.816
Just promise me
that you'll keep an open mind.

15:46.028 --> 15:48.610
All right?
About Boston and us and...

15:50.283 --> 15:52.239
...our little one.

15:53.703 --> 15:55.159
[CHUCKLES]

15:55.538 --> 15:57.494
-What?
-I'm pretty sure...

15:57.665 --> 16:00.281
...I put question marks
next to your name.

16:00.460 --> 16:01.575
-Did you?
-Yeah.

16:01.752 --> 16:04.368
That's weird because it looks like
you changed your mind.

16:05.173 --> 16:07.164
[le LAUGHING]

16:08.509 --> 16:11.125
Heh, heh. Oh, my God.

16:15.892 --> 16:18.178
RAYMOND:
I'm a violent man.

16:19.896 --> 16:23.013
I've taken on a life that requires it.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.899
I hurt people.

16:27.361 --> 16:29.192
I kill people.

16:30.156 --> 16:32.112
And each time I do...

16:32.283 --> 16:34.695
...in that moment...

16:35.620 --> 16:39.033
...another part of me dies
along with them.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.787
When I was young...

16:43.961 --> 16:48.421
...l romanticized the life of an outlaw.

16:48.591 --> 16:50.297
Bad guys.

16:54.013 --> 16:56.504
